, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Go Elon</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">He has commitment letters! Here=E2=80=
=99s Elon Musk=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com=
/click/27445764.287600/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRh=
LzAwMDE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIyMDQ4MTI4L3RtMjIxMzIyOWQxX3NjMTNkYS5odG0/607=
f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9b2a955c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsco=
pe" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impor=
tant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom=
-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">amended Schedule 13D</a>, updating =
his plans for Twitter Inc.:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Twi=
tter has not responded to the Proposal. Given the lack of response by Twitt=
er, the Reporting Person is exploring whether to commence a tender offer to=
 acquire all of the outstanding shares of Common Stock (together with the a=
ssociated rights issued pursuant to the Rights Agreement (the =E2=80=9CRigh=
ts=E2=80=9D and, together with the Common Stock, the =E2=80=9CShares=E2=80=
=9D)) that are issued and outstanding (and not held by the Reporting Person=
) at a price of $54.20 per share, net to the seller in cash, without intere=
st and less any required withholding taxes, subject to certain conditions (=
the =E2=80=9CPotential Offer=E2=80=9D), but has not determined whether to d=
o so at this time.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">To finance the Proposed =
Transaction or a Potential Offer, entities related to the Reporting Person =
have received commitment letters committing to provide an aggregate of appr=
oximately $46.5 billion as follows:</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">(i) A d=
ebt commitment letter, dated April 20, 2022 (the =E2=80=9CDebt Commitment L=
etter=E2=80=9D), from Morgan Stanley Senior Funding, Inc. and certain other=
 financial institutions party thereto as commitment parties (collectively, =
the =E2=80=9CCommitment Parties=E2=80=9D) pursuant to which the Commitment =
Parties have committed to provide $13 billion in financing to the Reporting=
 Person and related entities as follows: (a) a senior secured term loan fac=
ility in an aggregate principal amount of $6.5 billion, (b) a senior secure=
d revolving facility in an aggregate committed amount of $500 million, (c) =
a senior secured bridge loan facility in an aggregate principal amount of u=
p to $3 billion and (d) a senior unsecured bridge loan facility in an aggre=
gate principal amount of up to $3 billion ((a) =E2=80=93 (d) collectively, =
the =E2=80=9CDebt Facilities=E2=80=9D);</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">(ii=
) A separate debt commitment letter, dated April 20, 2022 (the =E2=80=9CMar=
gin Loan Commitment Letter=E2=80=9D), from Morgan Stanley Senior Funding, I=
nc. and certain other financial institutions party thereto as commitment pa=
rties (collectively, the =E2=80=9CMargin Loan Commitment Parties=E2=80=9D) =
pursuant to which the Margin Loan Commitment Parties have committed to prov=
ide $12.5 billion in margin loans (the =E2=80=9CMargin Loan Facility=E2=80=
=9D), the proceeds of which will be distributed or otherwise made available=
 to Purchaser; and</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">(iii) An equity commitme=
nt letter, dated April 20, 2022 (the =E2=80=9CEquity Commitment Letter=E2=
=80=9D), from the Reporting Person pursuant to which the Reporting Person h=
as committed to provide equity financing for the Proposed Transaction or th=
e Potential Offer sufficient to pay all amounts payable in connection with =
the Offer and the Merger (plus related fees and expenses), net of the amoun=
ts to be funded pursuant to the Debt Commitment Letter and the Margin Loan =
Commitment Letter, which is currently expected to be approximately $21 bill=
ion (the =E2=80=9CEquity Financing=E2=80=9D).</p></blockquote><p style=3D"m=
argin: 16px 0;">So there you go! Elon Musk needs about $46.5 billion to buy=
 Twitter at $54.20 per share: about $39.4 billion to pay for the 91% of Twi=
tter=E2=80=99s stock that he doesn=E2=80=99t currently own, about $4.3 bill=
ion of debt to refinance and various miscellaneous costs. To pay that, he h=
as:</p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 1=
6px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">A=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link=
.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27445764.287600/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvd=
i9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzAwMDE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIyMDQ4MTI4L3RtMjIx=
MzIyOWQxX2V4OTktYy5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB37140bb3" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">letter f=
rom his banks</a>=C2=A0offering to lend $13 billion to Twitter, if he buys =
it, with $7 billion of that coming in the form of senior secured bank loans=
 and $6 billion coming in the form of junk bonds.=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D=
"margin-bottom: 5px;">A=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/27445764.287600/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9k=
YXRhLzAwMDE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIyMDQ4MTI4L3RtMjIxMzIyOWQxX2V4OTktZC5odG0=
/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1bb54981" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"ite=
mscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !i=
mportant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bo=
ttom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">letter from his banks</a>=C2=A0=
offering to lend him $12.5 billion personally, secured by $62.5 billion wor=
th of his Tesla Inc. stock. At yesterday=E2=80=99s closing price, that come=
s to about 64 million shares, or about one-third of <a href=3D"https://link=
.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27445764.287600/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvd=
i9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzAwMDEzMTg2MDUvMDAwMDg5OTI0MzIyMDA2MjQwL3hzbEYz=
NDVYMDMvZG9jNS54bWw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB62f292bb" itemprop=3D"StoryLin=
k" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-=
decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color:=
 #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> his Tesla s=
take</a>.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">An <a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27445764.287600/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmd=
vdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzAwMDE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIyMDQ4MTI4L3RtMj=
IxMzIyOWQxX2V4OTktZS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc33fddb8" itemprop=3D"St=
oryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;=
 text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-=
color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> agree=
ment with himself</a> to put up the other $21 billion, give or take.</li></=
ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I want to discuss these things in more deta=
il but I should lead by saying: Good for him! These are real commitment let=
ters from real banks, or rather at least half of them are.[1] (The $21 bill=
ion is a commitment from himself to himself.) He =E2=80=A6=C2=A0seems to =
=E2=80=A6=C2=A0want to =E2=80=A6=C2=A0buy Twitter? When Musk sent Twitter=
=E2=80=99s board of directors a proposal to buy the company at $54.20 per s=
hare, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27445764.287=
600/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMTU=
vc3VyZS1lbG9uLW11c2stbWlnaHQtYnV5LXR3aXR0ZXI_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDQyMTIyX01PTkVZU1=
RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwN=
DIxJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1e28e2a9" item=
prop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color=
: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bord=
er-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #cc=
c;"> the stock=C2=A0<em>dropped</em></a>, because Musk=E2=80=99s casual off=
er and generally weird behavior did not seem to meaningfully increase the o=
dds that he was actually going to buy Twitter. I was skeptical myself. But =
this feels real? Twitter=E2=80=99s stock is barely changed as of 11 a.m. to=
day, but my own estimate of how likely it is that Musk will buy Twitter has=
 increased considerably.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Musk=E2=80=99s fil=
ing also says that his buyout proposal to the board, which was previously s=
ubject to financing and =E2=80=9Cbusiness due diligence,=E2=80=9D is no lon=
ger subject to those conditions. He has the financing, and if he is going t=
o launch a hostile tender offer he won=E2=80=99t be able to do much diligen=
ce first, so there=E2=80=99s no real reason for his merger proposal to be c=
ontingent on diligence. Also, you know, it=E2=80=99s Twitter, he more or le=
ss knows what he=E2=80=99s getting.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A few p=
oints about the financing. First, the traditional leveraged-buyout-type fin=
ancing, the $13 billion of debt that Musk plans to raise against Twitter. M=
usk attached the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2=
7445764.287600/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzAwMDE0=
MTgwOTEvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIyMDQ4MTI4L3RtMjIxMzIyOWQxX2V4OTktYy5odG0/607f07ceef4=
b8524a319a23cC37140bb3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targ=
et=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bo=
rder-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: =
solid; background-color: #ccc;">commitment letter and term sheet</a> to his=
 filing, so you can get a rough sense of the size and prices of these thing=
s:</p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16=
px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">There is a $6.5 billion term lo=
an with a rate of, roughly speaking, SOFR plus 4.75%. Three-month SOFR (the=
 term version of the Secured Overnight Financing Rate, as reported by CME G=
roup Benchmark Administration Limited) is about 0.95% today. (Musk can elec=
t to use one, three or six-month SOFR.) So that is roughly $370 million of =
interest cost per year.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">There=E2=
=80=99s a $500 million revolver with a commitment fee of 0.50% and a rate o=
f SOFR plus 4.5% on drawn amounts. So $30 million, if he draws the full rev=
olver.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">There is $6 billion of bond=
 financing, split evenly between secured and unsecured. The banks have comm=
itted to provide bridge loans: Ideally Twitter will sell the bonds before M=
usk=E2=80=99s deal closes, but if not the banks are on the hook to provide =
the money until the bonds can be issued to take out the bridge loans. The i=
nterest rates on the bonds are not specified =E2=80=94=C2=A0the banks have =
agreed to some maximum rate, but it=E2=80=99s in a fee letter that was not =
filed =E2=80=94=C2=A0but the rates on the bridge loans are SOFR plus 6.75% =
(secured) and SOFR plus 10% (unsecured). So that=E2=80=99s about another $5=
60 million of interest expense, if the bridge loans are drawn, and I am not=
 sure that Twitter can do junk bonds for much less than that.[2]</li></ol><=
p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So you are talking about a bit less than $1 bil=
lion of debt service costs for Twitter each year. Bloomberg reports that Tw=
itter=E2=80=99s estimated earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and=
 amortization are $1.43 billion for 2022 and $1.85 billion for 2023. So, uh=
, sure, doable! It is very unclear what Musk=E2=80=99s <em>business</em> pl=
an is for Twitter, and some of his statements =E2=80=94=C2=A0that he will=
=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27445764.287=
600/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9lbG9uLW11c2stc3VnZ2VzdHMtY2hhbmd=
lcy10by10d2l0dGVyLWJsdWUtc3Vic2NyaXB0aW9uLXNlcnZpY2UtMTE2NDk2MDU3Nzc/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cB4e4d0922" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">cut back on advertising</a>, <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27445764.287600/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cudGhldmVyZ2UuY29tLzIwMjIvNC8xNC8yMzAyNTM0My9lbG9uLW11c2stdHdpdHRlci10=
YWtlb3Zlci10ZWQtdGFsay1xdW90ZS1zdG9jay1idXlvdXQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa1=
c38616" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;">that he</a> =E2=80=9Cdoes not care about the economics at a=
ll=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94 might hint that Twitter=E2=80=99s EBITDA under Musk w=
ill be lower than the Bloomberg estimates. The margin for error seems slim.=
</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But I guess that=E2=80=99s fine? The thing=
 that classically happens, if a company borrows tons of money in a leverage=
d buyout and then doesn=E2=80=99t make enough money to service the debt, is=
 that the lenders get the company and the equity investors lose their inves=
tment.[3] Here, though, the equity investor is Elon Musk, and he=E2=80=99s =
putting in something like $33 billion of his own fortune, in the form of hi=
s equity commitment (i.e., money from himself) and the margin loan (i.e., h=
ocking his Tesla shares). He has a lot of incentive to make sure that Twitt=
er=E2=80=99s lenders get paid, or to pay them himself if it comes to that. =
As a leveraged buyout loan this package looks large and aggressive, but it =
is also a loan to the richest person in the world to finance a new toy that=
 he seems to really want, which probably helps the credit.</p><p style=3D"m=
argin: 16px 0;">Second, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/=
click/27445764.287600/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhL=
zAwMDE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIyMDQ4MTI4L3RtMjIxMzIyOWQxX2V4OTktZC5odG0/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cC1bb54981" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the Tesla margin loan</a>. Musk=C2=
=A0will have to post $62.5 billion of stock (a 20% loan-to-value ratio) to =
